After much consideration, we’ve made the decision to sunset NextPlace, Subnet 48.

While we believed NextPlace was a unique and innovative concept, the market ultimately didn’t agree. As incentives declined, so did Miner quality and data value. Our infrastructure and development costs began to exceed the potential incentive. Compounding this, our key data partnership faced persistent integrity issues, and despite our best efforts, we were unable to find strong product–market fit.

That said, we still firmly believe real estate data is an incredibly compelling use case for Bittensor. We simply didn’t get it right.

At Nickel5, our main focus is GAIA (Subnet 57), a subnet built to produce the best geospatial and weather AI in the world. We’re committed to making GAIA something Bittensor will be proud of: highest quality data, cutting-edge predictive accuracy, and a thriving ecosystem for Miners and Validators alike.
